> Mole isn't your ordinary Mexican spice blend. It contains onion, garlic, chiles,
> ground seeds such as sesame or pumpkin, and a secret ingredient: chocolate!
> Although the seasoning doesn't lend sweetness to the dish, it does contribute
> an irresistible richness.

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. (If you have a
microwave you can skip this step). Core, seed, and very thinly slice the
@poblano pepper{1}. Halve and peel the @red onion{1}. Thinly slice one half.
Finely dice the remaining half. Drain the @corn{1%can}. Cut the @lime{1} into
wedges. Toss the @beef sirloin tips{12%ounce} in a #medium bowl{} with
@molé spice blend{2%teaspoons}, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, and a large
pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add the poblano
and sliced onion. Cook, tossing, for ~{5-6%minutes}, until softened and
slightly charred. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from the pan and set
aside.

Make the corn salad: Heat another drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in the same
large pan over high heat. Add the diced onion. Cook ~{1-2%minutes}, until
slightly softened. Add the corn. Cook, tossing, for ~{3-4%minutes}, until lightly
charred. Season with salt, pepper, and as much @chili powder{1%teaspoon} as you
like. Remove from the pan and place in a medium bowl. Stir in @sour cream{2%tablespoons}
and one wedge of lime. Cover to keep warm.

Wrap the @flour tortilla{6} in #foil{} and place in the oven to warm
~{3-5%minutes}. Alternatively, wrap in a moistened #paper towel{} and warm for
~{30%seconds} in the microwave. Heat another drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}
in the same large pan over high heat. Add the steak tips and cook
~{3-4%minutes} per side, until browned.

In a #small bowl{}, stir together the remaining @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, a
squeeze of lime, and as much remaining mole spice and chili powder as you like
(start with a little and go up from there). Thin to a pourable consistency with
about @water{1%teaspoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Serve: Assemble the mole-spiced tacos with steak, poblano, onion, and crema.
Serve the Mexican corn salad on the side or in the tacos. Enjoy!